node.text: On the coast of Portugal, Gordon Ramsay visits one of the most unique vineyards on the planet where the vines grow in the sand. A new season of Gordon Ramsay: Uncharted airs Monday, May 31 at 9/8c.

node.title: Gordon Ramsay: Uncharted – A Vineyard in the Sand

node.text: Photo by @kahliaprilphoto / There is nothing better than being up high in the mountains to watch the sunset. The views never disappoint! This was taken in British Columbia, Canada.

node.text: Photo by @sofia_jaramillo5 / Franny Weikert cruises down a descent while bikepacking a route called A Swell Night Out through the San Rafael Swell Recreation Area in southeastern Utah. For four days we biked along the swell, a distinct geological area permeated by sharp, sudden upthrusts of rock that formed 40 to 70 million years ago. Geologic features from the Permian to Cretaceous periods, native endangered plants like the San Rafael cactus, and Native American pictographs and petroglyphs can all be seen in this unique area. #utah #geology #bikepacking

node.text: Photo by @mattborowick / If you’ve ever been to Yellowstone National Park, then you are all too familiar with this situation. Bison crossings are a daily adventure here, but for the safety of yourself and the animals, it is always better to stay in your vehicle. When entering the park, we were told to stay at least 75 to 100 feet (23 to 30 meters) away from the animals, but sometimes they decide to cross the road and back up traffic. If you are headed to Yellowstone this fall, make sure to heed the safety instructions of the park rangers; it may just save your life. Please follow @mattborowick for more pictures like this. #wyoming #yellowstonenp #nature #adventure #nationalparks

node.text:
Photo by @daisygilardini / In March the International Union for Conservation of Nature (IUCN) listed African forest elephants as critically endangered. The IUCN listed the more familiar African savanna elephants as endangered. Botswana’s government reopened legal elephant hunting in April and issued 287 new hunting licenses in that one month alone. Trophy hunters are willing to spend as much as $43,000 for the “thrill” of killing an elephant. 
Follow me @daisygilardini for more images and behind-the-scenes stories. #africa #botswana #elephant #conservation

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by National Geographic Travel on September 15, 2021. May be an image of 3 people, people standing and street.

node.text:
Photo by @dina_litovsky / In New York's Meatpacking District, slaughterhouses and gritty market stalls have given way to some of the flashiest nightclubs in the city. Between the velvet ropes and the taxi stands lies a theatrical world of courtship rituals and spontaneous street interactions. Each weekend night, young women wearing stilettos carefully navigate the district's cobblestone streets. I loved this candid moment of this young woman's partner helping her across the street. 
For more images, follow me @dina_litovsky.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by National Geographic Travel on September 15, 2021. May be an image of body of water and nature.

node.text:
Photo by Luján Agusti @lujanag / A boat navigates the waters of the Beagle Channel. Also known as Onashaga ("Sea of the Onas" in the Yagán language), the Beagle Channel is of great environmental importance locally and globally, since it concentrates 50 percent of the macroalgae forests that exist in Argentina. It is one of the great carbon sinks on the planet and harbors much biodiversity. 
Follow me @lujanag to learn more about my life and work on the southern island of Tierra del Fuego.

node.text: Photo by @juancristobalcobo / The Cauca, Colombia's second most important river, is seen here near the town of Puerto Valdivia in the department of Antioquia at a point where it flows with great strength. #riocauca #colombia #juancristobalcobo

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by National Geographic Travel on September 15, 2021. May be an image of 5 people, people standing, outdoors, crowd and tree.

node.text:
Photo by @joshuacogan / As an effigy is brought to the church at the center of Catarina, Nicaragua, the devoted gather to watch. I was struck by how the ficus trees, the same that surround the temples in Bali, also surround this place of worship. The ficus holds meaning in many faiths around the world. In Hinduism it is a place where sages sat, including the Buddha. It is a relative of the fig, which plays a role in the earliest scenes of the Old Testament, hiding humans' newfound shame. Some scholars believe it was the trees that were worshipped before the gods. 
For more images of rituals and the relationships between plants, humans, and spirituality, follow me @joshuacogan.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by National Geographic Travel on September 15, 2021. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
Photo by @stephen_matera / With almost 13,000 feet (3,962 meters) of vertical rise on the western side of the mountain, Mount Rainier is thousands of feet higher than anything else nearby. The vertical rise is large enough that Mount Rainier creates its own weather, as seen here where clouds form around the mountain on an otherwise clear day. 
Follow me @stephen_matera for more images like this from Mount Rainier National Park and around the world.  #volcano #nationalpark #lenticularcloud

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by National Geographic Travel on September 14, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and nature.

node.text: Photo by @sofia_jaramillo5 / Three bikepackers watch the sunset during a bikepacking trip near the San Rafael Swell in southeastern Utah. I find bikepacking to be the perfect pace for travel in the American West. I can see more of a place than I can while backpacking, but it’s a bit slower paced than a road trip. I feel more freedom and independence when relying on my own body to get from one place to the next, and I think more about my connection to the environment I’m traveling through. #bikepacking #utah #travel

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by National Geographic Travel on September 14, 2021. May be an image of nature and arctic.

node.text: Photo by @kiliiiyuyan / Hoarfrost coats sea ice at the edge where it meets the Arctic Ocean in Alaska. This kind of ice forms when humid air settles on the sea ice and immediately freezes, creating ice crystals in beautiful formations. It’s a bad sign in the early spring, when temperatures should be far below freezing around-the-clock. #ice #arctic #alaska
